<p>The <a href="/wiki/Green%E2%80%93Tao_theorem" title="Green–Tao theorem">Green–Tao theorem</a> implies that there are arbitrarily large magic squares consisting of primes.
</p><p>The following "reversible magic square" has a magic constant of 264 both upside down and right way up:<sup id="cite&#95;ref-65" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-65"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>65<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
